Eduardo Soriano writes ("mount automatic file system check counter"):
> Hello guys,
> 
> I would like to know how to modify or tourn around the mount counter used by
> mount command to start an automatic file system check.
> 
> When mounting a file system during system bootstart, I got from time
> to  time a message saying the file system has reached count value
> and will be checked.
'man tune2fs'
Be careful about disabling it - I've seen corruption caused by
hardware (esp. RAM) failure; the check is an important guard against
further damage.
Peter
